This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training a sentiment analysis model using crawled movie review data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of sentiment analysis in predicting psychological states, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves human participants and their psychological measurements, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
